The paper discusses the formal analysis of cryptographic properties of distributed systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also presents a formal theory for specifying and verifying distributed systems, which involves logical reasoning and theorem proving (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a semi-automatic theorem prover, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the correctness of system components, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with distributed systems, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
